Carl Froch has expressed his desire to fight Julio Cesar Chavez Jr in Las Vegas . 
  The former middleweight world champion was stopped in nine rounds by Andrzej Fonfara . 
  Chavez was outclassed by the Polish fighter at the StubHub Center in California . 
  Froch had said he wanted to fight Chavez Jr but that now looks unlikely . 
  He has not fought since knocking out George Groves last May . 
 